<div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">nintendo2600 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">All the pins are presant on the edge of the PCB so I should be good if in fact it does use ram as you suspect and I have to enable the write line.<br /></div><br />I don't really "suspect" anything, I was just assuming the header was correct, in which case the program would use CHR-RAM. But since Memblers appears to know the programs you are talking about it would be wise to trust him. =)<br /><br />But if you ever want to turn a CHR-ROM cart into a CHR-RAM one, a PCB with all the pins on the edge is indeed ideal. A lot of MMC3 boards, for example, don't have pin 56, which is the CHR write signal.</div><br /><br />Thanks for the info.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3870">nintendo2600</a> — Tue Aug 09, 2011 9:39 pm</p><hr />
